<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900515-0021</DOCNO><DOCID>900515-0021.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Apple Bancorp Inc.:   Holders Requested to Reject   Proxy Fight by Bidder Stahl</HL><DATE>05/15/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   APK</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)</IN><LP>   Apple Bancorp Inc. urged shareholders to reject a proxyfight organized by Stanley Stahl and affirmed its rejectionof the New York real-estate investor's $38-a-share tenderoffer.   The New York-based parent of Apple Bank for Savings toldshareholders in a letter, &quot;We believe that it is coercive forMr. Stahl to condition his offer on having you first vote togive him control&quot; of Apple before the board &quot;has had a fullopportunity to explore and pursue financially more-attractivealternatives.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   Mr. Stahl, who controls 30.6% of Apple and has offered$121.6 million for the rest, declined to comment on theletter, which Apple disclosed as part of a Securities andExchange Commission filing. The company and Mr. Stahl havelawsuits pending against each other.   Apple's directors haven't set a date for the annualmeeting; Mr. Stahl's lawsuit demands, among other things,that the board set such a date. The company has said that theboard hasn't set the date in order to allow time to explorealternatives to Mr. Stahl's bid.   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,Apple shares closed at $44, unchanged.</TEXT></DOC>